<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <title>HTML Answers</title>
    <style>
        /* Page background */
        body {
            background-color: #ffe4ec; /* soft pink */
        }

        /* Style rule for hover effect */
        a.favorite-link:hover {
            background-color: lightblue;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>

    <h2>Difference Between "alt" and "title" Attributes</h2>
    <p>
        The <strong>alt</strong> attribute is used in images to provide alternative text if the image cannot be displayed. 
        It is also important for accessibility, as screen readers use it to describe the image to visually impaired users.
    </p>
    <p>
        The <strong>title</strong> attribute provides additional information about an element. 
        It is usually displayed as a tooltip when the user hovers over the element.
    </p>

    <h2>Dictionary Definition Markup Example</h2>
    <p>
        <dfn>HTML</dfn> is defined as:
    </p>
    <blockquote>
        "HyperText Markup Language (HTML) is the standard markup language for creating web pages."
    </blockquote>

    <h2>Favorite Website Link with Hover Style</h2>
    <p>
        Visit my favorite site: 
        <a href="https://www.wikipedia.org" class="favorite-link" title="Go to Wikipedia">Wikipedia</a>
    </p>

    <footer>
        <p>Footer</p>
    </footer>

</body>
</html>
